SDL version.

* Fade the colors in and out.

* Setting keys (the whole name<->key mapping).

* Zoom.

* thrustrc SDL defaults.


X version.

* Fade the colors in and out.

* Take away the demand for a local colormap if it isn't absolutly
  necessary.

* Ports for other unices.
  HP-UX, Solaris, SunOS, OpenBSD, AIX, Ultrix, OSF1, Irix and Linux are known
  to work.

* Support for non 8 bpp pseudocolor visuals.

* Caps lock seem to be buggy.


Windows version.

* Sound.

* Display of error messages during startup.

* Screen is not redrawn when switching back to thrust from some other
  application.

* thrust dies when minimized.


General

* Should not require GNU make.

* Music.

* The blinking of the stars.

* Rewrite of the scrolling routines (Needed, but how?).

* Steering with joystick.

* Documentation of the code.

* Remove all sorts of arbitrary limits when parsing levels.

* Load levels at run-time.

* Save keyboard configuration in .thrustrc.

* Use GGI/GII instead of SVGAlib or X.
